==English==

===Etymology===
Irish Gaelic ''spàg'' - the paw or limb or claw of an animal, ''transf.'' to humans as pejorative or for [[club-foot]]

===Noun===
'''spaug'''
# a pejorative term for a foot

===Quotations===
*'''1922''': Taking off his flat '''spaugs''' and the walk. &mdash; James Joyce, '''Ulysses'''